386→                        <div id="content">Let $k(N)$ denote the size of the largest set $A\subseteq \{1,\ldots,N\}$ such that the sets\[S_r = \{ a_1+\cdots +a_r : a_1&#60;\cdots&#60;a_r\in A\}\]are disjoint for distinct $r\geq 1$. Estimate $k(N)$ - in particular, is it true that $k(N)\sim 2N^{1/2}$?</div>
387→                        <div id="problem_id"><a href="/874">#874</a>: <a href="#cite-Er62c-874" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('Er62c','874'); return false;">[Er62c]</a><a href="#cite-Er98-874" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('Er98','874'); return false;">[Er98]</a></div>
